The OAI-PMH Shell Harvester is able to harvest OAI-PMH targets. It supports multiple configurable targets which can be updated individually. Deletes are not supported fully, they are saved as empty files.

Using shell-harvester:

1. Configure the harvester
   Edit the paths in the config.xml file, 
   records are stored in <recordpath>/<repository_id>/harvested .

2. Configure a repository
   Edit a repository in the config.xml file,
   a set and a conditional is not required.

3. Run the harvester
   $ ./harvester.sh <repository_id>
